# using Docker Containers

## Create/run React Vite

```bash
npm create vite@latest Web-components
cd Web-components
npm install
npm run dev -- --host 0.0.0.0 --port 7775
```

Open:

```bash
http://localhost:7775
```

## Create Dockerfile

In the project root, create a file named Dockerfile:

```bash
FROM node:22-alpine

WORKDIR /app

COPY package*.json ./

RUN npm install

COPY . .

EXPOSE 8083

CMD ["npm", "run", "storybook", "--", "--host", "0.0.0.0", "--port", "8083"]
```

## Create .dockerignore

```bash
node_modules
dist
.git
```

## Build Docker image

```bash
docker build -t web-component .
```

## Run Docker container on port 8083

```bash
docker run --name lastName_firstName_coding_assignment11 -p 8083:8083 web-component
```

Open:

```bash
http://localhost:8083
```

# Installation of others libaries

## Storybook Installation

Storybook was installed to provide component documentation, interactive controls, and isolated component development.

```bash
npx storybook@latest init

Storybook runs using:

npm run storybook

Default URL:

http://localhost:6006
```

## Styled Components Installation

Styled Components was installed to provide component-level styling.

```bash
npm install styled-components

Type definitions were installed for TypeScript support.

npm install -D @types/styled-components
```

Styled Components were used instead of CSS files to encapsulate styling within each component.

## Testing Setup

Vitest was selected as the testing framework because the project uses Vite.

Required packages were installed:

```bash
npm install -D vitest
npm install -D @testing-library/react
npm install -D @testing-library/jest-dom
npm install -D jsdom
```
